product_name: Kiehl's Since 1851Ultra Facial Cream with Squalane
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackThe Kiehl's Since 1851 Ultra Facial Cream with Squalane has a unique lightweight texture and lasting 72-hour hydration to leave skin softer and visibly healthier.
details: DetailsBenefitsThis non-greasy moisturizer is clinically demonstrated to hydrate 15 layers deep for softer, smoother, and healthier-looking skinParaben-free & fragrance freeUltra Facial Cream has received the National Eczema Association's Seal of AcceptanceKey IngredientsSqualane: a highly-refined botanical lipid derived from olives; with an exceptional affinity to skin, it absorbs easily and is known to help replenish skin's barrier keeping it soft, supple, and moisturizedGlacial Glycoprotein: originally sourced from Antarctic sea glaciers; helps to deeply hydrate and maintain skin's moisture balancePro-Ceramides: help to reinforce skin's barrier strength and help skin better resist external disruptorsResearch ResultsProvides lasting 72-hour hydration for soft, smooth, healthy-looking skin*Strengthens skin's barrier and hydrates up to 15 surface layers deep**Repairs the skin barrier in just 1 hour***Absorbs into skin easily with an ultra-lightweight textureTested in everyday and extreme environmentsNow in a 125ml lightweight jar with 40% less plasticFor all skin types, including sensitive skin*72-hour hydration results based on an instrumental study.**In the stratum corneum. Based on an instrumental study vs untreated skin*** Barrier repair results based on an instrumental study on tape-stripped skin.Item 2540233How To UseAfter cleansing and toning, apply a dime-sized amount of Kiehl's hydrating facial cream to skin. Use twice daily, both day and night as the ultimate compliment to your skincare routine.IngredientsAqua / Water, Glycerin, Dimethicone, Squalane, Bis-Peg-18 Methyl Ether Dimethyl Silane, Sucrose Stearate, Stearyl Alcohol, Peg-8 Stearate, Myristyl Myristate, Prunus Armeniaca Kernel Oil / Apricot Kernel Oil, Phenoxyethanol, Persea Gratissima Oil / Avocado Oil, Glyceryl Stearate, Cetyl Alcohol, Oryza Sativa Bran Oil / Rice Bran Oil, Olea Europaea Fruit Oil / Olive Fruit Oil, Chlorphenesin, Stearic Acid, Palmitic Acid, Carbomer, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Prunus Amygdalus Dulcis Oil / Sweet Almond Oil, Xanthan Gum, Ethylhexylglycerin, Sodium Hydroxide, Tocopherol, Glycine Soja Oil / Soybean Oil, Pseudoalteromonas Ferment Extract, Myristic Acid, Hydroxypalmitoyl Sphinganine, Salicylic Acid, Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil / Sunflower Seed Oil, Rosmarinus Officinalis Leaf Extract / Rosemary Leaf Extract, Citric Acid.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: After cleansing and toning, apply a dime-sized amount of Kiehl's hydrating facial cream to skin. Use twice daily, both day and night as the ultimate compliment to your skincare routine.

reviews.headline: Basic but so good for me
reviews.comments: I have normal to dry skin, acne and sensitive. Im usually a Biosassance moisturizer but needed something a tad lighter. This was it especially during hot days for me. I usually get it on sale! The texture feels like cross breed with gel moisturizer and a heavy moisturizer. It does contain dimethicone for that slip. My skin was not irritated to it!

reviews.headline: LOVE LOVE LOVE
reviews.comments: Love the feeling very light

reviews.headline: My favorite moisturizer
reviews.comments: This has become my favorite moisturizer & have been using it for a few years now. I have tried SO many others but always come back to this one. I do have one other favorite but this one is best for me & for my sensitive skin, lightweight & soothing.

reviews.headline: Works wonders!
reviews.comments: My sikn turns read very easily even if a product is for sensitive skin! But this right here did not disappoint!! Little goes a long way!!!! Definitely worth every cent! No irritation or burning AT ALL which is hard to find for my skin! Just made my second purchase.

reviews.headline: Perfect face cream!
reviews.comments: I ran out a face cream I used to use  and needed a face cream really bad and quick so I stopped at ulta and came across KIEHL'S face cream. I read the reviews on the ulta app and saw that it had many good reviews and its good for sensitive skin, so I bought it. once I applied the face cream to my face, I fell in love with the cream! I have sensitive skin so I always get scared if a face cream will start burning my skin but this was smooth, super hydrating, hydration lasts all day, and no smell at all which is perfect. This is my new face cream and little goes a long way!

reviews.headline: i love it
reviews.comments: this brand is amazing

reviews.headline: I always come back
reviews.comments: This is a very reliable moisturizer for me. I already know it works for my sensitive skin and doesnt break me out. I dont consider it the most moisturizing cream that i tried but it gets the job done. Also works great under makeup.

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: This product wasnt as thick as I would've liked it but it absorbs well and is for dry skin. This is definitely an everyday face moisturizer.

reviews.headline: It Works
reviews.comments: This works real well for my skin. I've tried other products and none have worked as well as this one. It's a little expensive, but for me a little goes a long way. I have super picky and sensitive skin, and this was the moisturizing answer it needed. The texture is really nice and creamy, it doesn't pill, and there is almost no noticeable smell to it.

reviews.headline: Pores
reviews.comments: Emphasized my pores and blackhead, not worth it especially for the price point.

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: This product is a miracle, I had undergone radiation treatment for cancer and that had left my skin super dry and after using Kiehl's after a week I've noticed a dramatic difference.

reviews.headline: Effective basic moisturizer ï¿¼
reviews.comments: It's definitely a no-frills but quality moisturizer, so unsure why it's so expensive. Will be looking for other options that are cheaper but would pick up if a good sale.

reviews.headline: Left skin super Hydrating!
reviews.comments: I really enjoy this product cause i was suffering with dry skin and now it's super hydrating and soft. I like it's not greasy at all and there's no fragrance.

reviews.headline: Best Face Moisturizer
reviews.comments: My daughter and I love this product. We do the 30min drive to Ulta in a different town just to buy it. Definitely beats the other creams we have tried.

reviews.headline: bro
reviews.comments: it broke me out really bad

reviews.headline: My new favorite moisturizer
reviews.comments: I was a Peter Thomas Roth water drench cream fan for its light feel and hydration, but it's expensive. I thought this give Kielhs a try and I love it (and the lower price!).

reviews.headline: Helpful
reviews.comments: I use to have to shave my face everyday to get all the access skin off because of my acutane making my skin dry, this moisturizer helped a lot. I was able to put on makeup with out it being patchy, it is VERYY thick and best for over night use.

reviews.headline: Yes
reviews.comments: Great product

reviews.headline: Nothing Remarkable
reviews.comments: Soooo I've got dry skin. This is a new thing for me as I spent 24 years having oily skin and then BAM you hit 25 and it's dry. Now I'm a black girl and if its one thing my momma taught me it was how to moisturize. I don't feel like this product does enough for it to be priced the way it is. I do not feel it offers superior moisture or leaves my skin looking better than my KPL LPS lotion. It's nice sure, feels great, but what are the real benefits that make it worth so much? I've been using this for about 6 months now and I just dont feel like it's giving me the moisture.

reviews.headline: GET IT NOW!!
reviews.comments: I love this product! Helps with break outs. I haven't broke out in months! And my face is so glowy!

faceoff_positive.comments: I have been using moisturizers since I was 12 but never found one that's really suit me. Ultra Facial Cream is my very first product I got from Kiehl's and I fell in love with it! Because I just moved to America, my dry skin is getting worse:( So my friend and internet sources recommended me to this goody. It hydrates my skin wonderfully and I can feel it the first morning after I applied this cream. This sounds not right but it did and my sister agreed with me. I would recommend everyone to try this cream out.
faceoff_positive.headline: Swear by this product!

faceoff_negative.comments: I've been using this product for years and love it. I was shocked when I looked at the ingredients taped to the bottom of the jar for the first time today...it contains parabens. A serious buzzkill for my image of Kiehl's as a 'healthy' brand. So, all excellent, except that if it has parabens, it's value to me is zero. Please consider reformulating.
faceoff_negative.headline: Ugly surprise
